snippet.textDisplay: I love and appreciate my emo days. It helped me a lot to deal with hard ships and my emotions. You really did express your self as an emo without having to say it.  The music, the styles, your friends, the concerts all just made me feel better because I was the quiet girl and this was myself expression. Now as an adult, even tho I do still like black clothing( I’ve been adding color to my clothing over the last 10 years lol), listen to it, and done my makeup a bit more “emo” on days where I feel it. But over all I am more confident now, I talk a lot to other, and more about my self. This to me is because of my “emo” days. I have evolved into my own and my music has expanded and I still say Thank you to emo culture. Glad it’s still alive 🎸😎😍
